      <Meanings>
        <Meaning id="556ce723-952b-4ee6-9371-74eb1e7d8f26" type="Noun">
          <Vi>thấu kính</Vi>
          <En>A piece of transparent material, usually glass or plastic, with at least one curved surface that is used to focus light or magnify images.</En>
          <Example>The camera’s lens focuses light onto the sensor to capture a sharp image.</Example>
          <IsArchaic>false</IsArchaic>
          <Situations>
            <Situation id="3b2cfc6c-e5d2-4d9b-a8f0-db8ef7963100">
              <Vi>Trong máy ảnh hoặc kính hiển vi, bộ phận quang học làm cong ánh sáng để tạo hình ảnh.</Vi>
              <En>In a camera or microscope, the optical component that bends light to form an image.</En>
            </Situation>
            <Situation id="d160ff00-ffa2-4699-9974-8af2127a7efa">
              <Vi>Kính mắt có thấu kính điều chỉnh độ cận hoặc viễn.</Vi>
              <En>Glasses or contact lenses that correct vision by refracting light.</En>
            </Situation>
          </Situations>
        </Meaning>
